In article <313sks$fjh@garuda.csulb.edu>, jeff@csulb.edu (Jeff Shih) writes:
> for all you cryptology experts, what beginning book would you recommend 
> for learning how to program and understand ciphers?
> Mostly number theory and pseudeocode, written well.
> What textbooks should i look for?
> 
   I suggest "A Course in Number Theory and Cryptography" by Neal Koblitz.
Although the "dedication" is a real howler (I don't have a copy in front of me,
but it is dedicated to mathematics students in numerous _former_ Socialist-bloc
countries) I think it is one of the best mathematical introductions to the
subject. Includes pseudo-code too.

JS

